quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  1,1,"In the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful"
  1,2,"All Praise belongs to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds"
  1,3,"The Beneficent, the Merciful"
  1,4,The Ruler of the Day of Judgment
  1,5,Thee alone we serve and Thee alone we ask for aid
  1,6,Guide us in the Straight Path
  1,7,The path of those whom Thou hast favoured; Not of those who earn Thy wrath; nor of those who go astray
  2,1,ALIF LAM MIM
  2,2,This is the Book! There is no doubt therein; a guide to the pious
  2,3,"Who believe in the unseen, and are steadfast in worship, and spend of what We have given them"
  2,4,"Who believe in what is revealed to you (Muhammad), and what was revealed before you, and are sure of the Hereafter"
  2,5,"These are guided by their Lord, and these are the successful"
  2,6,"Verily, those who disbelieve, it is the same to them if you warn them or if you warn them not, they will not believe"
  2,7,"Allah has set a seal upon their heart and on their hearing; and on their eyes is dimness, and for them is grievous woe"
  2,8,"And there are those among men who say, \"We believe in Allah and in the last day;\" but they do not believe"
  2,9,They would deceive Allah and those who do believe; but they deceive only themselves and they do not perceive
  2,10,"In their heart is a sickness, and Allah has made them still more sick, and for them is grievous woe because they lied"
  2,11,"And when it is said to them, \"Do not evil in the earth,\" they say, \"We do only what is right"
  2,12,Are not they the evildoers? And yet they do not perceive
  2,13,"And when it is said to them, \"Believe as other men believe,\" they say, \"Shall we believe as fools believe?\" Are not they themselves the fools? And yet they do not know"
  2,14,"And when they meet those who believe, they say, \"We do believe;\" but when they go aside with their devils, they say, \"We are with you; we were but mocking"
  2,15,"Allah shall mock at them and let them go on in their rebellion, blindly wandering on"
  2,16,"Those who buy error for guidance, their traffic profits not, and they are not guided"
  2,17,"Their likeness is as the likeness of one who kindles a fire; and when it lights up all around, Allah goes off with their light, and leaves them in darkness that they cannot see"
  2,18,"Deaf, dumb, blind, and they shall not return"
  2,19,"Or like a storm-cloud from the sky, wherein is darkness and thunder and lightning; they put their fingers in their ears at the thunder-clap, for fear of death, for Allah encompasses the disbelievers"
  2,20,"The lightning well-nigh snatches off their sight, whenever it shines for them they walk therein; but when it is dark for them they halt; and if Allah willed He would go off with their hearing and their sight; verily, Allah is mighty over all"
  2,21,O you folk! Serve (adore) your Lord (Guardian) who created you and those before you; per chance (or possibly) you may fear evil (learn righteousness)
  2,22,"Who made the earth for you a bed and the heaven a canopy; and sent down from heaven water, and brought forth therewith fruits for your sustenance; so make no peers (rivals) for Allah, when you know better"
  2,23,"And if you are in doubt of what we have revealed unto Our servant, then bring a chapter like it, and call your witnesses other than Allah if you tell truth"
  2,24,"But if you do it not - and you surely cannot - then fear the Fire whose fuel is men and stones, prepared for disbelievers"
  2,25,"But bear the glad tidings to those who believe and work righteousness, that for them are Gardens beneath which rivers flow; whenever they are provided with fruit there from they say, \"This is what we were provided with before,\" and they shall be"